channel.name: How many fields does Encryption.encrypt produce?

messages.content:
From what i've gathered from the encrypt implementation, it should work like this:
- UInt64 is 1 Field
- Encrypted UInt64 will be [Field, Field]

is this correct?

Hey Matej, I didn't want to say something incorrect, but since no one else answered, here's what I think:

The size of the ciphertext is the size of the message plus one.  The extra field element is the authentication tag of the message.

https://github.com/o1-labs/snarkyjs/blob/841a6693412dd9e006e46664791885ffa73571fd/src/lib/encryption.ts#L15

messages.content: Yes yes, thats what i figured from the code hence why i said UInt64 encrypted would not be just 1 field, but +1 therefore two fields
However i was not able to get encrypt/decrypt working, im sure i am using the same keypair to encrypt & decrypt, but i get an assertion error on decryption.
i can produce a reproducible example but i haven't dived into that yet
Yes, based on my practice, I think you are right, the assertion error you mentioned may be caused by this bug:  https://github.com/o1-labs/snarkyjs/issues/442
